args: Looks like our guy went into that house.\nWhat's our next move?
Perhaps we can avail ourselves of a\npeep through that window.
Nothing weird, really...\nHey, wait, there's something written on\nthe floor.
It is a magic sigil, drawn in blood.
It must have required a fair amount\nof blood to paint all... Oh!
The exsanguination incidents.\nI think it's time for us to have a chat\nwith this particular fellow.
I'll go to the front door—you guys watch\nthe windows and back to make sure\nhe doesn't slip away.
I am struck by one minor point of\nconcern, {player_name}.
If possible, I should like to research the\nmatter straight away. Might I leave this\nscene to you for the moment?
A small matter involving the sigil that I\nhope is naught but idle worry.

However, if my fears prove true, this
becomes a somewhat more vexing case.
I feel it would be best to know before
proceeding further.
In that case, go ahead. We'll rendezvous\nas soon as we secure the suspect.
All right, time to catch our mark.
We'll hear what he has to say for himself,\nthen check in with Akasha.
...Then you admit to it? You made the\nsigil and drained all the blood?
Yes! All was done so I might\nsee this sigil completed!
What does it DO, exactly? The energy it\ngives off is exceptionally unpleasant...
It is the key to eternal life!
Of a sort. To be more specific, it's a\nsummoning circle for a particular fiend.
If I can bind it to my will and share its\npower, I will never grow old! Never die!\n...Or that was the plan, at least.
I am not fond of the ＂was＂ portion in that\nparticular sentence. Did the spell fail?
Oh, the spell worked like a charm—but the\nmoment the thing appeared, it took off\nwithout so much as a look back!
But I won't be humiliated like this!\nI'm going to track that thing down,\nand when I do, I'll—
Right! Okay, then. I think we understand\nwhat's going on now. I take it you have\nsome way to find this thing?

Would I be standing here if I did?!
I heard rumors earlier, but that turned out
to just be some woman in a costume that
people were fawning over.
Which explains how irritated you were\nwhen you saw her and realized she wasn't\nthe creature you were looking for.
So you're NOT a vampire wannabe.
But why bother with the costume and\ntrappings of a vampire in that case?
Costume? What are you talking about?
Don't try to muddy the waters now.\nThe victims all reported that their\nassailant wore a costume.
And who told you that? The cows?\n'Cause I haven't attacked any people.
Wait, wait, wait. What's going on here?\nIf HE didn't attack them, then who did?
You know, this reminds me of a story\nabout a certain creature...
Hey, yeah! Didn't you read me a story\nabout an immortal monster thingie once?
An immortal monster that seduced victims,\ndrank their blood, and turned them into\none of its own kind.
Stop. You're not actually suggesting that—
That those villagers weren't attacked by\na person in a costume? Yes, Cleo.\nThat's exactly what I'm suggesting.
(If memory serves, that sigil is the\nforbidden vampiric summoning circle.)
(The source is indistinct, but I sense\notherworldly mana, which means the\ncreature is most certainly here.)
Ah, but your beauty is captivating.
